              <h2>How the Alabama local sales tax calculator works</h2>
              <p>
                Alabama has a 4% state sales tax, and most cities and counties
                add their own local sales and use taxes on top of that. This
                calculator lets you:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  Enter the <strong>state, county, and city rates</strong> you
                  find from official sources.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Calculate tax from a <strong>pre-tax amount</strong> or work
                  backwards from a
                  <strong>total that already includes tax</strong>.
                </li>
                <li>
                  See a clear <strong>breakdown</strong> of state vs. local tax.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Compare two Alabama locations</strong> for the same
                  purchase amount.
                </li>
              </ul>

              <h3>Formulas used</h3>
              <div class="formula-box text-sm">
                <p class="font-semibold mb-1">1. Combined tax rate</p>
                <p>Let:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>\( r_s \) = state rate (e.g. 4%)</li>
                  <li>\( r_c \) = county rate</li>
                  <li>\( r_m \) = municipal (city) rate</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Convert to decimals and sum:</p>
                <p>\[ r_{\text{total}} = \frac{r_s + r_c + r_m}{100} \]</p>
                <p class="font-semibold mt-3 mb-1">2. From pre-tax amount</p>
                <p>If \( A_{\text{net}} \) is the price before tax:</p>
                <p>
                  \[ \text{Tax} = A_{\text{net}} \times r_{\text{total}} \] \[
                  A_{\text{gross}} = A_{\text{net}} + \text{Tax} \]
                </p>
                <p class="font-semibold mt-3 mb-1">
                  3. From total (tax included)
                </p>
                <p>
                  If \( A_{\text{gross}} \) is the total price including tax:
                </p>
                <p>
                  \[ A_{\text{net}} = \frac{A_{\text{gross}}}{1 +
                  r_{\text{total}}} \] \[ \text{Tax} = A_{\text{gross}} -
                  A_{\text{net}} \]
                </p>
              </div>

              <h2>Step-by-step: using the calculator</h2>
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <strong>Look up your local rates.</strong>
                  <p>
                    Use the Alabama Department of Revenue or your city/county
                    website to find the current state, county, and city sales or
                    use tax rates for your address.
                  </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Enter the purchase amount.</strong>
                  <p>
                    Choose whether the amount is <em>before tax</em> or
                    <em>includes tax</em> using the “Calculation type” dropdown,
                    then enter the dollar amount.
                  </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Enter state, county, and city rates.</strong>
                  <p>
                    The state rate defaults to 4%. Adjust county and city rates
                    to match your jurisdiction. The calculator shows the
                    combined rate automatically.
